      },
      "date": "2018-07-17 15:14:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt looks that mdt_layout_change() releases the lock taken, instead of return it to client like open does. IMHO it's more efficient, though that lock is EX mode, which needs to downgrade to CR mode before returning to client.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "138f29263de1ce049fe14fbca686ae8e86c219ee",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 622,
        "name": "Qian Yingjin",
        "email": "qian@ddn.com",
        "username": "qian"
      },
      "date": "2018-07-17 15:35:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think we should not return EX layout lock to a client. And taking EX layout lock, changing layout and releasing EX layout lock on the MDT is part of executing the intent. After executed the extent, the lock server on MDS will enqueue the CR lock and grant the lock to the client.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
